        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:53:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/53/71",
        "text": [
          " اَلصَّلاَةِ اَلْفَرِيضَةِ قَائِماً فَيَنْسَى كِيسَهُ أَوْ مَتَاعَهُ يَخَافُ ضَيْعَتَهُ أَوْ هَلاَكَهُ قَالَ «يَقْطَعُ صَلاَتَهُ وَ يُحْرِزُ مَتَاعَهُ» قَالَ قُلْتُ فَتَفَلَّتُ عَلَيْهِ دَابَّتُهُ فَيَخَافُ أَنْ تَذْهَبَ أَوْ يُصِيبَهُ فِيهَا عَنَتٌ فَقَالَ «لاَ بَأْسَ أَنْ يَقْطَعَ صَلاَتَهُ وَ يُحْرِزَ وَ يَعُودَ إِلَى صَلاَتِهِ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.1071 - Sama’a ibn Mehran asked him about a man who is performing the obligatory prayer while standing and forgets his bag or belongings, fearing they might be lost or damaged.\nImam (as) said: \"He may cut his prayer and secure his belongings.\"\nSama’a then said: \"What if his animal breaks loose and he fears it might run away or cause harm?\"\nImam (as) said: \"It is no problem for him to cut his prayer, secure his animal, and then return to his prayer.\""
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1063,
        "local_index": 2,
        "narrator_chain": {
          "parts": [
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "1068 - وَ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "سَأَلَ مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ مُسْلِمٍ أَبَا جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ:"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " عَنِ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "اَلرَّجُلِ تُؤْذِيهِ اَلدَّابَّةُ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " وَ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "هُوَ يُصَلِّي"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " قَالَ"
            }
          ]
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:53:2",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/53/1068",
        "text": [
          " «يُلْقِيهَا عَنْهُ إِنْ شَاءَ أَوْ يَدْفِنُهَا فِي اَلْحَصَى."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.1068 - Muhammad ibn Muslim asked Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) about a person who is harmed by an animal while he is praying.\nHe (as) replied: \"He should throw it away from him if he wishes, or bury it in the pebbles.\""
          ]
        }
      },
