        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:53:5",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/53/1072",
        "text": [
          " اَلصَّلاَةِ فَيَرَى حَيَّةً بِحِيَالِهِ هَلْ يَجُوزُ لَهُ أَنْ يَتَنَاوَلَهَا وَ يَقْتُلَهَا قَالَ «إِنْ كَانَ بَيْنَهَا وَ بَيْنَهُ خُطْوَةٌ وَاحِدَةٌ فَلْيَخْطُ وَ يَقْتُلُهَا وَ إِلاَّ فَلاَ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.1072 - Ammar al-Sabati asked him about a man who is in prayer and sees a snake in front of him. Is it permissible for him to step forward and kill it?\nImam (as) said: \"If there is just one step between him and the snake, then he may step forward and kill it; otherwise, he should not.\""
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1067,
        "local_index": 6,
        "narrator_chain": {
          "parts": [
            {
