            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "أَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " قَالَ"
            }
          ]
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:53:6",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/53/1073",
        "text": [
          ": «إِذَا كُنْتَ فِي صَلاَةِ اَلْفَرِيضَةِ فَرَأَيْتَ غُلاَماً لَكَ قَدْ أَبَقَ أَوْ غَرِيماً لَكَ عَلَيْهِ مَالٌ أَوْ حَيَّةً تَتَخَوَّفُهَا عَلَى نَفْسِكَ فَاقْطَعِ اَلصَّلاَةَ وَ اِتْبَعْ غُلاَمَكَ أَوْ غَرِيمَكَ وَ اُقْتُلِ اَلْحَيَّةَ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.1073 - Hariz narrated from Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) who said:\n\"If you are in the obligatory prayer and you see one of your servants who has run away, or a debtor to whom you owe money, or a snake that you fear for your life, then break your prayer, follow your servant or debtor, and kill the snake.\""
          ]
        }
      }
